00:24:33.170 --> 00:24:36.500
I had a meeting with Jerry, my
editor, and a couple of other

00:24:36.500 --> 00:24:40.140
publicity people about the book
coming out, and what I

00:24:40.140 --> 00:24:42.150
was supposed to do and
everything like that.

00:24:42.150 --> 00:24:43.730
They were talking about all the
promotional efforts they

00:24:43.730 --> 00:24:46.990
were going to do.

00:24:46.990 --> 00:24:50.030
And I was like, so, is there
anything that I can do between

00:24:50.030 --> 00:24:54.310
now and the book coming out,
Jerry, to help the book sell,

00:24:54.310 --> 00:24:56.660
to help its profile?

00:24:56.660 --> 00:24:59.320
And he just looked at me-- like
this tweedy Bret Easton

00:24:59.320 --> 00:25:01.280
Ellis David Foster Wallace
dude-- and he was just like,

00:25:01.280 --> 00:25:03.430
