And the most that you get out
of most people in New

00:34:49.120 --> 00:34:50.820
York is like, huh.

00:34:50.820 --> 00:34:52.639
Anyway.

00:34:52.639 --> 00:34:54.679
Or a stockbroker dude being
like, listen, who's

00:34:54.679 --> 00:34:55.480
paying for all this?

00:34:55.480 --> 00:34:57.398
Because that's what they want
to know-- like, what are you

00:34:57.398 --> 00:34:57.930
doing, what's the angle?

00:34:57.930 --> 00:34:59.960
Which happens a lot.

00:34:59.960 --> 00:35:04.410
And as we're going along, I see
Matt Besser, one of the

00:35:04.410 --> 00:35:07.070
founders of the theater, run
onto the lawn and start

00:35:07.070 --> 00:35:08.770
throwing flyers at all these
people that are sunning

00:35:08.770 --> 00:35:09.560
themselves.

00:35:09.560 --> 00:35:11.620
And some people would look at
them and some people wouldn't,

00:35:11.620 --> 00:35:13.130
and he'd just start screaming
at them--

00:35:13.130 --> 00:35:15.160
don't just be curious!

00:35:15.160 --> 00:35:17.150
Don't just be curious!

00:35:17.150 --> 00:35:19.560
Which is, when you think about
it, one of the most important

00:35:19.560 --> 00:35:22.530
tenets of, I guess, marketing,
creativity, anything, is

00:35:22.530 --> 00:35:24.730
trying to get people to
not just be curious.

00:35:24.730 --> 00:35:26.550
Because I know I do
this all day.

00:35:26.550 --> 00:35:27.720
You get a link to something.

00:35:27.720 --> 00:35:28.540
This is pretty cool.

00:35:28.540 --> 00:35:29.580
Oh, Boing Boing.

00:35:29.580 --> 00:35:30.700
Oh, it's a TomTom.

00:35:30.700 --> 00:35:32.140
Anyway, I'll buy that later.

00:35:32.140 --> 00:35:33.460
And then they never do.

00:35:33.460 --> 00:35:36.600
And the biggest thing that you
have to conquer is the idea of

00:35:36.600 --> 00:35:39.330
people strictly being curious,
which is what most people are

00:35:39.330 --> 00:35:41.340
satisfied to do, to pick
something up and go, huh,

00:35:41.340 --> 00:35:43.830
cool, anyway, and move on.

00:35:43.830 --> 00:35:48.430
And that is still something that
I'm trying to conquer.

00:35:48.430 --> 00:35:52.350
And with Sword Club, we
did it a little bit.

00:35:52.350 --> 00:35:56.160
The movie never turned into like
a overnight theatrical

00:35:56.160 --> 00:36:00.000
sensation, but it has since
picked up an afterlife on DVD.

00:36:00.000 --> 00:36:02.280
It was on Netflix for a while.

00:36:02.280 --> 00:36:04.180
Now it's on Hulu.

00:36:04.180 --> 00:36:07.400
Maybe it wants to
be on YouTube?

00:36:07.400 --> 00:36:10.300
Legally.

00:36:10.300 --> 00:36:15.760
So I realized that this sort of
thing has an outer limit.

00:36:15.760 --> 00:36:18.320
When I was in Phoenix, and we
were still doing Sword Club,

00:36:18.320 --> 00:36:20.120
it had become this weird
ritual at this point.

00:36:20.120 --> 00:36:22.710
We'd go to whatever Walmart
was in our town.

00:36:22.710 --> 00:36:24.050
We would sit down
with the swords.

00:36:24.050 --> 00:36:27.430
We would look up inspirational
quotes and be like, Elvis

00:36:27.430 --> 00:36:32.990
said, and just do it like
a job at that point.

00:36:32.990 --> 00:36:36.990
I ended up being in Arizona
all alone by myself doing

00:36:36.990 --> 00:36:38.560
these Q&amp;As, because that's
where I'm from, and I was

00:36:38.560 --> 00:36:39.560
staying with my family.

00:36:39.560 --> 00:36:42.740
And I was getting a burrito one
night, and I saw a tattoo

00:36:42.740 --> 00:36:43.960
parlor across the road.

00:36:43.960 --> 00:36:45.820
And I was like, that's
the next step--

00:36:45.820 --> 00:36:47.780
Tattoo Club.

00:36:47.780 --> 00:36:49.400
I was like, if people
come 10 times--

00:36:49.400 --> 00:36:51.200
10 times--

00:36:51.200 --> 00:36:55.420
I will get their name tattooed
somewhere on my body.

00:36:55.420 --> 00:36:57.440
And so I announced
it that night.

00:36:57.440 --> 00:36:58.880
And I was basically--

00:36:58.880 --> 00:37:01.240
I don't know if you guys have
ever seen the documentary

00:37:01.240 --> 00:37:03.780
"Hearts of Darkness" about
Francis Ford Coppola making

00:37:03.780 --> 00:37:05.210
"Apocalypse Now?" You should
check it out if you haven't.

00:37:05.210 --> 00:37:06.800
But that's where I was at--

00:37:06.800 --> 00:37:09.650
like Francis Ford Coppola mid
shooting "Apocalypse Now." I'm

00:37:09.650 --> 00:37:11.650
like, tattoos, that'll
make it happen.

00:37:11.650 --> 00:37:14.160
That'll take us over the top.

00:37:14.160 --> 00:37:15.890
And so I announced it.

00:37:15.890 --> 00:37:18.890
And then I was like, no one's
going to do it, right?

00:37:18.890 --> 00:37:20.070
Three kids.

00:37:20.070 --> 00:37:22.320
Three kids went to the
movie 10 times.

00:37:22.320 --> 00:37:24.580
And I was like, OK, cool, and
went back to LA and was like,

00:37:24.580 --> 00:37:26.680
I have to get a tattoo now.

00:37:26.680 --> 00:37:28.860
And I kept in touch with them,
and after about a year, I was

00:37:28.860 --> 00:37:30.390
like, guys, I can't get it.

00:37:30.390 --> 00:37:31.220
I can't do it.

00:37:31.220 --> 00:37:32.250
I just can't.

00:37:32.250 --> 00:37:33.650
I'll make it up to
you somehow.

00:37:33.650 --> 00:37:36.770
And then they're thanked
in my new book.

00:37:36.770 --> 00:37:39.330
I apologize to them in the
acknowledgements section--

00:37:39.330 --> 00:37:40.540
Tattoo Club, by name--

00:37:40.540 --> 00:37:43.930
and I plan to do it pretty much
with every book since,

00:37:43.930 --> 00:37:46.330
because that's the only
permanent thing I have to

00:37:46.330 --> 00:37:47.030
offer anyone.

00:37:47.030 --> 00:37:48.525
Because nobody wants
to be on my thigh.

00:37:51.370 --> 00:37:51.770
So--

00:37:51.770 --> 00:37:54.710
AUDIENCE: You should do it.

00:37:54.710 --> 00:37:55.920
DC PIERSON: [LAUGHING]

00:37:55.920 --> 00:37:56.710
I can't.

00:37:56.710 --> 00:37:58.110
I can't do it.

00:37:58.110 --> 00:37:59.830
I have to do so many
nude scenes.

00:37:59.830 --> 00:38:00.245
I'm sorry?

00:38:00.245 --> 00:38:01.670
AUDIENCE: [INAUDIBLE].

00:38:01.670 --> 00:38:03.120
DC PIERSON: Fair enough.

00:38:03.120 --> 00:38:03.570
Totally.

00:38:03.570 --> 00:38:07.046
You could say that
about anything.

00:38:07.046 --> 00:38:08.890
AUDIENCE: [INAUDIBLE].

00:38:08.890 --> 00:38:11.330
DC PIERSON: Oooooooh!

00:38:11.330 --> 00:38:13.360
For those of you watching at
home, that guy just said, a

00:38:13.360 --> 00:38:15.040
lot of people say it, not a
lot of people ever do it.

00:38:15.040 --> 00:38:16.290
Fair enough, sir.

00:38:21.630 --> 00:38:25.890
I am, like I said, a stand-up
and an author and an actor.

00:38:25.890 --> 00:38:28.590
And I started doing storytelling
stuff.

00:38:28.590 --> 00:38:31.760
I do a storytelling show called
"DC Pierson is Bad at

00:38:31.760 --> 00:38:35.030
Girls," about how bad
I am at girls.

00:38:35.030 --> 00:38:38.550
I started rapping a little bit
on some of Donald's early

00:38:38.550 --> 00:38:40.860
albums, because I'm a huge hip
hop fan, and it was something

00:38:40.860 --> 00:38:42.150
that I'd always wanted to do.

00:38:42.150 --> 00:38:45.170
And so I still get the
occasional Twitter at reply

00:38:45.170 --> 00:38:48.280
from somebody being
like, you suck.

00:38:48.280 --> 00:38:49.790
And a few people being
like, you're awesome.

00:38:49.790 --> 00:38:52.590
But a lot of people being like,
why did you do that?

00:38:52.590 --> 00:38:55.810
Um, serious.

00:38:55.810 --> 00:38:59.670
And when it came time to sell
this new book, "Crap Kingdom,"

00:38:59.670 --> 00:39:03.160
to people in general, I was
like, what do I do?

00:39:03.160 --> 00:39:07.310
I don't have a lot of money
to hire a publicist.

00:39:07.310 --> 00:39:08.660
I'm all these different
things.

00:39:08.660 --> 00:39:11.850
How do I explain that to people,
and make it into

00:39:11.850 --> 00:39:13.060
something that is appealing
to them,

00:39:13.060 --> 00:39:14.580
instead of just confusing?

00:39:14.580 --> 00:39:16.810
Because it seems like it could
be a lot of messages.

00:39:16.810 --> 00:39:22.910
And what I realized about what
I wanted to do with this book

00:39:22.910 --> 00:39:28.585
in terms of actually getting
people to buy it was all of

00:39:28.585 --> 00:39:30.010
that stuff.

00:39:30.010 --> 00:39:31.260
All of the stuff.

00:39:34.160 --> 00:39:37.820
And I've been living my life for
the past almost 10 years

00:39:37.820 --> 00:39:40.720
now with a bunch of different
irons in the fire, and going,

00:39:40.720 --> 00:39:42.550
like, when one of these irons
gets hot enough, then I'll be

00:39:42.550 --> 00:39:45.190
rich, and that'll finance doing
all these other things.

00:39:45.190 --> 00:39:47.090
And it hasn't happened yet.

00:39:47.090 --> 00:39:52.260
And what I realized is that
instead of kind of just going

00:39:52.260 --> 00:39:54.100
like, OK, it's just going to
be one of these irons from

00:39:54.100 --> 00:39:55.200
here on out--

00:39:55.200 --> 00:39:56.100
I have these irons.

00:39:56.100 --> 00:39:58.290
They've all been in the
fire for a long time.

00:39:58.290 --> 00:39:59.430
They're pretty hot.

00:39:59.430 --> 00:40:00.830
They really are.

00:40:00.830 --> 00:40:02.180
They're all pretty hot.

00:40:02.180 --> 00:40:06.310
And at this point, I'm
like, fuck the fire.

00:40:06.310 --> 00:40:07.375
My irons are hot.

00:40:07.375 --> 00:40:09.260
They're the fire now.

00:40:09.260 --> 00:40:12.180
My irons are the fire.

00:40:12.180 --> 00:40:16.230
And to that end, what I've been
doing to promote this

00:40:16.230 --> 00:40:18.330
book, to get people to pre-order
it, among other

00:40:18.330 --> 00:40:21.810
things, is if anybody pre-orders
my book before

00:40:21.810 --> 00:40:26.060
March 7, which is this coming
Thursday, I've been writing

00:40:26.060 --> 00:40:30.240
their names, their full names,
into custom rap songs that I

00:40:30.240 --> 00:40:33.320
then perform and
put on YouTube.

00:40:33.320 --> 00:40:35.310
I've done 100 so far.

00:40:35.310 --> 00:40:37.650
I do 50 names per song.

00:40:37.650 --> 00:40:40.980
And people seem to enjoy it.

00:40:40.980 --> 00:40:44.130
And it is that thing of being,
like, don't just be curious.

00:40:44.130 --> 00:40:46.320
It's that thing of fighting the
weed and the doughnuts,

00:40:46.320 --> 00:40:47.570
and being like, wouldn't
you rather have

00:40:47.570 --> 00:40:48.840
a custom rap instead?

00:40:48.840 --> 00:40:51.570
And the book, coming out March
7, which is really good and

00:40:51.570 --> 00:40:52.820
funny, and you'll like it.

00:40:54.890 --> 00:40:57.390
And it's been going
pretty well.

00:40:57.390 --> 00:41:00.700
I owe a lot of raps,
but they're coming.

00:41:00.700 --> 00:41:02.190
I wrote the third one, finished

00:41:02.190 --> 00:41:04.200
the third one yesterday.

00:41:04.200 --> 00:41:06.280
And it's been great.

00:41:06.280 --> 00:41:08.560
It's been really, really,
really, really cool.

00:41:08.560 --> 00:41:11.980
A couple of the other things
that I'm doing in terms of my

00:41:11.980 --> 00:41:14.010
various irons--

00:41:14.010 --> 00:41:16.670
I had like 30 minutes of
stand-up up that I've

00:41:16.670 --> 00:41:19.070
developed over the past couple
years, just to try to be a

00:41:19.070 --> 00:41:21.340
stand-up and to try to get on
TV, try to get famous for

00:41:21.340 --> 00:41:23.470
doing stand-up and whatever.

00:41:23.470 --> 00:41:27.760
And this year, I auditioned
to try to get a special on

00:41:27.760 --> 00:41:28.330
television.

00:41:28.330 --> 00:41:29.450
Didn't happen.

00:41:29.450 --> 00:41:31.550
And I was mad about it, because
I was like, this is

00:41:31.550 --> 00:41:31.940
really good.

00:41:31.940 --> 00:41:32.990
I worked really hard.

00:41:32.990 --> 00:41:35.230
You know, how the yearbook staff
will do in high school,

00:41:35.230 --> 00:41:36.800
when you're like, my name is
misspelled, and they're like,

00:41:36.800 --> 00:41:39.250
yeah, but we work really hard!

00:41:39.250 --> 00:41:40.460
But I was like, I did
work really hard.

00:41:40.460 --> 00:41:41.100
I'm really proud of it.

00:41:41.100 --> 00:41:42.600
I want to put it out there.

00:41:42.600 --> 00:41:44.390
And I was like, oh, I have
this book coming out.

00:41:44.390 --> 00:41:45.410
How do those two
things relate?

00:41:45.410 --> 00:41:49.630
And I was like, oh, if enough
people pre-order the book,

00:41:49.630 --> 00:41:51.900
I'll put the stand
up out there.

00:41:51.900 --> 00:41:53.100
And that's what I'm
doing right now.

00:41:53.100 --> 00:41:56.260
I'm having an offer where if 100
people pre-order the book,

00:41:56.260 --> 00:41:59.280
I'll put that stand-up special
for free on YouTube.

00:41:59.280 --> 00:42:01.220
And I'm about a quarter of
the way there, and I

00:42:01.220 --> 00:42:03.580
announced it yesterday.

00:42:03.580 --> 00:42:08.340
And again with the rap stuff,
there have been for every five

00:42:08.340 --> 00:42:10.190
people that are like, you suck,
there's one guy that's

00:42:10.190 --> 00:42:11.740
like, when are you going
to put out a mix tape?

00:42:11.740 --> 00:42:14.770
And I wrote and recorded one
over the course of like two

00:42:14.770 --> 00:42:17.180
years just completely as a
hobby, because I know there's

00:42:17.180 --> 00:42:18.825
a lot of people that are like,
you suck, but there's one dude

00:42:18.825 --> 00:42:20.290
that's being like, you're
all right, man.

00:42:20.290 --> 00:42:22.500
And I was doing it
for that kid.

00:42:22.500 --> 00:42:23.160
And I did it.

00:42:23.160 --> 00:42:26.280
And I announced if 50 people
pre-order my book, I'll put

00:42:26.280 --> 00:42:29.200
out my first mix tape, like that
one kid has been saying

00:42:29.200 --> 00:42:30.270
he wanted all those years.

00:42:30.270 --> 00:42:31.280
And they did.

00:42:31.280 --> 00:42:32.100
It happened last week.

00:42:32.100 --> 00:42:33.270
50 more people pre-ordered it.

00:42:33.270 --> 00:42:36.300
They sent me their receipts to
crapkingdom@gmail.com, which

00:42:36.300 --> 00:42:37.870
is where you send your receipt
if you want your name written

00:42:37.870 --> 00:42:41.030
into a custom rap song.

00:42:41.030 --> 00:42:41.845
And they did.

00:42:41.845 --> 00:42:43.390
And I put the mix tape out.

00:42:43.390 --> 00:42:44.530
And it's been getting
feedback.

00:42:44.530 --> 00:42:45.960
And have a track on there
where I'm like,

00:42:45.960 --> 00:42:47.840
please buy my book.

00:42:47.840 --> 00:42:49.760
And when I put the stand-up out
there, it's going to come

00:42:49.760 --> 00:42:51.880
with a little wrapper on it
that's me being-- not a rapper

00:42:51.880 --> 00:42:54.000
like rapper, but a wrapper like
a little bumper at the

00:42:54.000 --> 00:42:56.150
beginning-- it's like,
please buy my book.

00:42:56.150 --> 00:42:57.450
I'm putting this out
there for free.

00:42:57.450 --> 00:43:00.510
Or if you have already
bought it, thank you.

00:43:00.510 --> 00:43:01.980
I did the same thing with
my storytelling show.

00:43:01.980 --> 00:43:03.330
I taped it a couple weeks ago.

00:43:03.330 --> 00:43:05.880
And next week, I'm going to
announce that if 100 people

00:43:05.880 --> 00:43:08.040
pre-order my book, I'll
put it out there.

00:43:08.040 --> 00:43:13.390
And it is kind of my little
homemade way of trying to

00:43:13.390 --> 00:43:17.940
create the feeling that movies
or TV shows or celebrities can

00:43:17.940 --> 00:43:21.010
create because they have money
and time, and they can be

00:43:21.010 --> 00:43:21.840
everywhere.

00:43:21.840 --> 00:43:24.000
I'm trying to, for those people
that have been checking

00:43:24.000 --> 00:43:25.660
for me over the years-- that
one kid who's like, you're

00:43:25.660 --> 00:43:26.650
pretty all right--

00:43:26.650 --> 00:43:29.210
I'm trying to create that
feeling for him of, like,

00:43:29.210 --> 00:43:31.140
here's all the stuff I've
been working on.

00:43:31.140 --> 00:43:33.200
Here's all the irons
in the fire.

00:43:33.200 --> 00:43:36.530
And then on March 7, they get
a book, and I think they're

00:43:36.530 --> 00:43:37.510
going to like it.

00:43:37.510 --> 00:43:43.490
And I didn't realize it
until I sat down to

00:43:43.490 --> 00:43:45.645
prepare this today.

00:43:48.584 --> 00:43:54.010
But it feels very appropriate
to me to kind of finally be

00:43:54.010 --> 00:43:58.140
opening all of the portal doors
and letting all of the

00:43:58.140 --> 00:44:01.190
gnomes and elves and dragons
from my various worlds that

00:44:01.190 --> 00:44:03.480
I've been cultivating over the
years, let them pour out and

00:44:03.480 --> 00:44:06.900
let them help me try to have
a lot of people read

00:44:06.900 --> 00:44:08.090
and enjoy this book.

00:44:08.090 --> 00:44:10.810
It feels appropriate, because
the book is about the problems

00:44:10.810 --> 00:44:13.620
of living in two worlds, and
I've been living the problems

00:44:13.620 --> 00:44:14.770
of living in a lot of different

00:44:14.770 --> 00:44:16.940
worlds for many years.

00:44:16.940 --> 00:44:19.590
And I like that I'm finally
bringing it all together.

00:44:19.590 --> 00:44:21.060
Hopefully, I think it's
going pretty well.

00:44:21.060 --> 00:44:23.860
I like that I'm bringing it all
together to actually sell

00:44:23.860 --> 00:44:25.760
this book that is about
living in two worlds.

00:44:25.760 --> 00:44:34.950
And sort of, I guess, in
summation, I realized in

00:44:34.950 --> 00:44:38.240
preparing this speech
that I wouldn't--

00:44:38.240 --> 00:44:41.010
because I've had to over the
years, or sometimes just in my

00:44:41.010 --> 00:44:42.510
mind and sometimes out loud--

00:44:42.510 --> 00:44:47.620
defend the idea that I need to
do all these things that I do,

00:44:47.620 --> 00:44:49.690
when maybe I should
just do one and

00:44:49.690 --> 00:44:52.240
wouldn't that be enough?

00:44:52.240 --> 00:44:56.680
But everything is everything,
and I wouldn't be all of the

00:44:56.680 --> 00:44:59.420
things that I am without-- or
I wouldn't be any of the

00:44:59.420 --> 00:45:02.680
things that I am without being
all of the things that I am.

00:45:02.680 --> 00:45:07.340
And lions are cool, and witches
are cool, but you

00:45:07.340 --> 00:45:11.010
wouldn't get to see any of
them without a wardrobe.

00:45:11.010 --> 00:45:14.980
And to paraphrase "Pulp
Fiction," I am trying real

00:45:14.980 --> 00:45:18.700
hard to be the wardrobe.

00:45:18.700 --> 00:45:19.600
Thanks,

