00:45:37.750 --> 00:45:39.390
them all very well.

00:45:39.390 --> 00:45:43.820
Have you ever ventured into sort
of your own crap kingdom?

00:45:43.820 --> 00:45:47.160
Is there a world that you have
tried to sort of occupy, and

00:45:47.160 --> 00:45:47.850
it didn't go great?

00:45:47.850 --> 00:45:48.620
Because it seems like--

00:45:48.620 --> 00:45:49.390
DC PIERSON: Well, I write
for award shows a lot.

00:45:49.390 --> 00:45:49.880
AUDIENCE: What was that?

00:45:49.880 --> 00:45:50.940
DC PIERSON: I write for
award shows a lot.

00:45:50.940 --> 00:45:53.790
AUDIENCE: [LAUGHING]

00:45:53.790 --> 00:45:55.625
DC PIERSON: For scratch,
for money.

00:45:55.625 --> 00:45:58.790
No, but even that is kind of
fun, because I get a lot of

00:45:58.790 --> 00:46:01.300
great stories out
of it and stuff.

00:46:01.300 --> 00:46:04.020
I met Gary Busey once.

00:46:04.020 --> 00:46:05.880
That was exciting.

00:46:05.880 --> 00:46:13.320
No, I mean, I don't know.

00:46:13.320 --> 00:46:16.560
I guess as far as the things
that I don't want to do, I

00:46:16.560 --> 00:46:23.200
hesitate to write a lot of stuff
where I'm shitting on

00:46:23.200 --> 00:46:25.190
things that other people do,
because I feel like there's

00:46:25.190 --> 00:46:26.530
enough of that out there.

00:46:26.530 --> 00:46:30.200
And I definitely know people
that are artists and do, on

00:46:30.200 --> 00:46:32.530
their Twitter feeds, like, this
sucks, or this whatever.

00:46:32.530 --> 00:46:35.260
I guess I do a little bit of
that, but it always feels like

00:46:35.260 --> 00:46:37.670
a., just sort of on a practical
level, you could

00:46:37.670 --> 00:46:39.950
potentially alienate people who
might later employ you, so

00:46:39.950 --> 00:46:44.050
just from a coward's point of
view, I don't like to do that.

00:46:44.050 --> 00:46:45.190
I try not to do that.

00:46:45.190 --> 00:46:47.320
Sometimes I can't help it.

00:46:47.320 --> 00:46:52.160
But then also, it seems like
really bad karmic strategy, in

00:46:52.160 --> 00:46:57.480
terms of putting that out there,
and then if somebody

00:46:57.480 --> 00:46:59.345
were to do that to me, I'd be
like, hey, man, come on.

00:46:59.345 --> 00:47:02.360
I'm just trying to
make a thing.

00:47:02.360 --> 00:47:06.140
But there haven't, thankfully,
been too many things that I

00:47:06.140 --> 00:47:13.460
have gone full bore into that
I haven't liked or wanted to

00:47:13.460 --> 00:47:15.716
stick around for.

00:47:15.716 --> 00:47:18.870
I mean, certain relationships.

00:47:18.870 --> 00:47:20.894
But yeah.

00:47:20.894 --> 00:47:22.295
It's a great question.

00:47:22.295 --> 00:47:24.170
Yes.

