00:47:46.360 --> 00:47:50.790
DC PIERSON: [LAUGHING]

00:47:50.790 --> 00:47:51.670
Oh, nice!

00:47:51.670 --> 00:47:52.920
OK, that guys just said henna.

00:47:52.920 --> 00:47:54.170
Yeah, totally.

00:47:56.790 --> 00:47:57.880
That's a really good question.

00:47:57.880 --> 00:47:59.460
So what you're saying,
basically, is that if I were

00:47:59.460 --> 00:48:00.855
to actually get the tattoos--

00:48:03.770 --> 00:48:10.200
which are owed to Jeremy
Seeliger, Darryl Seeliger, and

00:48:10.200 --> 00:48:16.430
Jason Artigas, whose names
are tattooed in here--

00:48:16.430 --> 00:48:18.500
that that would enrich
my artistic process.

00:48:22.150 --> 00:48:23.500
I don't know that it would.

00:48:23.500 --> 00:48:35.450
And it just seemed like a lot
to explain to a girl on a

00:48:35.450 --> 00:48:36.700
third date, hopefully?

00:48:39.460 --> 00:48:43.440
Why do you have three
dudes' names?

00:48:43.440 --> 00:48:45.220
However you dress them up--

00:48:45.220 --> 00:48:47.380
you can put them in flames
coming out of a motorcycle

00:48:47.380 --> 00:48:51.270
being driven by a dragon,
but they're still--

00:48:51.270 --> 00:48:52.320
yeah, I don't know.

00:48:52.320 --> 00:48:53.640
I don't think I can do it.

00:48:53.640 --> 00:48:56.000
I think I'm going to have to
continue putting them in the

00:48:56.000 --> 00:48:58.210
acknowledgements of
things, or working

00:48:58.210 --> 00:48:59.060
their names into things.

00:48:59.060 --> 00:48:59.820
And I think they're
cool with that.

00:48:59.820 --> 00:49:00.860
We talk over email.

00:49:00.860 --> 00:49:02.220
I think they're all
right with it.

00:49:02.220 --> 00:49:03.730
I don't think any of them
are too mad at me.

00:49:06.250 --> 00:49:08.000
One of the guys was like,
yeah, I get it.

00:49:08.000 --> 00:49:08.220
It's cool.

00:49:08.220 --> 00:49:11.400
He was like, I didn't expect
you to actually do it.

00:49:11.400 --> 00:49:14.611
And then I was like,
maybe I will do it.

00:49:14.611 --> 00:49:15.970
Does that make sense?

00:49:15.970 --> 00:49:17.850
AUDIENCE: [INAUDIBLE]

00:49:17.850 --> 00:49:19.317
DC PIERSON: I got some good
orange water here.

00:49:24.790 --> 00:49:30.420
AUDIENCE: So I was wondering,
do you see your lifestyle as

00:49:30.420 --> 00:49:33.300
something that might be viable
for others in the future, like

00:49:33.300 --> 00:49:37.540
a multi-talented individual
that doesn't have to be

00:49:37.540 --> 00:49:40.670
monolithically Hollywood
centralized famous but can

00:49:40.670 --> 00:49:43.530
still make a living off
of kind of more

00:49:43.530 --> 00:49:46.230
democratized media?

00:49:46.230 --> 00:49:48.180
DC PIERSON: That's
a great question.

00:49:48.180 --> 00:49:52.300
I was just, again, thinking
about this last night, when I

00:49:52.300 --> 00:49:56.090
was prepping.

00:49:56.090 --> 00:50:02.100
Because the whole reason that I
have been doing all of this

00:50:02.100 --> 00:50:03.770
pre-order campaign and
everything like that is

00:50:03.770 --> 00:50:05.650
because I do want the book
to be a success.

00:50:05.650 --> 00:50:08.330
I want it to really be a thing
where it's like, this is a

00:50:08.330 --> 00:50:10.470
"New York Times" best
selling everything.

00:50:10.470 --> 00:50:15.980
I do want that, in a very,
very I guess cynical--

00:50:15.980 --> 00:50:19.610
or not cynical, but just very
singularly focused, Daniel Day

00:50:19.610 --> 00:50:23.360
Lewis in "There Will Be Blood."
Not that I'll smash

00:50:23.360 --> 00:50:28.270
somebody's head in over
it, but I do want it

00:50:28.270 --> 00:50:30.550
to be a real success.

00:50:30.550 --> 00:50:31.250
I do.

00:50:31.250 --> 00:50:34.630
It's just that I don't know of
any other way to build that

00:50:34.630 --> 00:50:38.400
except for using all of the
other stuff that I've done.

00:50:38.400 --> 00:50:40.930
I don't think it would be
terribly effective to take out

00:50:40.930 --> 00:50:45.912
a bank loan to buy $20,000 worth
of Facebook banners.

00:50:45.912 --> 00:50:48.450
I do feel like the best way that
that sort of thing can

00:50:48.450 --> 00:50:50.200
spread is somebody being
like, hey, look at

00:50:50.200 --> 00:50:54.510
this, to their friend.

00:50:54.510 --> 00:50:56.000
Hey, come check this thing out,
because they're given

00:50:56.000 --> 00:50:57.550
away swords.

00:50:57.550 --> 00:50:58.800
Sweet.

00:51:01.830 --> 00:51:04.460
But I do think that that's
definitely a viable option,

00:51:04.460 --> 00:51:09.790
and it's something that, as much
as I am still listening

00:51:09.790 --> 00:51:12.160
to Jerry Howard in my head being
like, just get famous,

00:51:12.160 --> 00:51:15.050
doesn't matter for what, no--

00:51:15.050 --> 00:51:17.830
I mean, I'm in an Allstate
commercial, dude.

00:51:17.830 --> 00:51:21.160
It doesn't matter for what.

00:51:21.160 --> 00:51:22.410
It really doesn't.

00:51:24.780 --> 00:51:27.630
I do think that-- let's say none
of that stuff happens.

00:51:27.630 --> 00:51:31.990
Let's say that it sort of
comes out and it doesn't

00:51:31.990 --> 00:51:34.180
immediately hit the top of the
charts, which is very unlikely

00:51:34.180 --> 00:51:36.680
that it will, as much
stuff as I've tried.

00:51:36.680 --> 00:51:39.220
It's just really, really, really
mysterious, and the

00:51:39.220 --> 00:51:41.590
algorithm that they
use to compile it

00:51:41.590 --> 00:51:43.830
is shrouded in mystery.

00:51:43.830 --> 00:51:46.340
Although maybe it doesn't
have to be--

00:51:46.340 --> 00:51:46.725
dcpierson@gmail.com.

00:51:46.725 --> 00:51:47.975
Hit me up, Google employes.

00:51:50.820 --> 00:51:54.090
But if it doesn't happen, I was
thinking about it, and I

00:51:54.090 --> 00:51:58.620
was like, oh, this sort of
campaign architecture that

00:51:58.620 --> 00:52:02.120
I've put in place in a very sort
of haphazard jury rigged

00:52:02.120 --> 00:52:05.030
kind of way throughout trying to
put this pre-order campaign

00:52:05.030 --> 00:52:07.960
together, it doesn't go away
once the book comes out.

00:52:07.960 --> 00:52:10.400
If anything, it continues to
help me stay in touch with

00:52:10.400 --> 00:52:11.260
those people.

00:52:11.260 --> 00:52:13.580
And all I have in terms
of people that

00:52:13.580 --> 00:52:14.770
go and by the book--

00:52:14.770 --> 00:52:17.550
most people that go and buy the
book, when they email me

00:52:17.550 --> 00:52:20.170
about it, they aren't buying it
just because they heard me

00:52:20.170 --> 00:52:21.300
on a single podcast and they've

00:52:21.300 --> 00:52:22.630
never heard of me before.

00:52:22.630 --> 00:52:24.970
Although that's happening
in some cases.

00:52:24.970 --> 00:52:27.940
Or they're seeing a single
tweet or whatever.

00:52:27.940 --> 00:52:31.470
It's that they have seen a
tweet by somebody, maybe

00:52:31.470 --> 00:52:36.460
somebody famous they follow, and
they remember me from when

00:52:36.460 --> 00:52:37.940
they were watching Derrick
videos when they were in

00:52:37.940 --> 00:52:41.730
college, like this point
like seven years ago.

00:52:41.730 --> 00:52:42.960
And it's great.

00:52:42.960 --> 00:52:44.710
It really is.

00:52:44.710 --> 00:52:46.870
Every time I can get in front
of your face is awesome,

00:52:46.870 --> 00:52:49.110
whether that's in the Allstate
commercial or whether that's

00:52:49.110 --> 00:52:52.800
in a dick and fart video from
seven years ago or whatever,

00:52:52.800 --> 00:52:56.480
it all sort of when you see that
next thing, where it's

00:52:56.480 --> 00:52:57.900
like, oh, that guy again.

00:52:57.900 --> 00:52:59.440
It all sort of builds to that.

00:52:59.440 --> 00:53:00.770
And so I do think that--

00:53:00.770 --> 00:53:03.215
let's say it isn't just a smash
out of the gate success.

00:53:06.020 --> 00:53:11.080
I will get to continue to do
these kinds of things, for

00:53:11.080 --> 00:53:11.760
their own sake.

00:53:11.760 --> 00:53:15.100
And I wouldn't even be getting
to do the strategy that I'm

00:53:15.100 --> 00:53:19.310
talking about, where I put out a
mix tape and a special and a

00:53:19.310 --> 00:53:22.430
storytelling show and whatever,
if I hadn't been

00:53:22.430 --> 00:53:25.990
doing those things over the
past five years just

00:53:25.990 --> 00:53:29.120
for their own sake.

00:53:29.120 --> 00:53:32.840
I guess the short
answer is yes.

